  {
    "ts": "2026-04-21T21:08:00+00:00",
    "headline": "Tractor Supply Is Today’s Worst S&P 500 Stock. Here’s Why.",
    "summary": "Shares of  Tractor Supply  sank on Tuesday, making it the worst performing S&P 500 component in the session, after the farm supplier missed Wall Street’s expectations for the first quarter on weaker pet product sales but kept its full-year guidance steady.  Tractor Supply  announced first-quarter earnings of 31 cents a share, compared with 34 cents a share a year ago, with revenue increasing 3.4% to $3.59 billion.  Wall Street expected the company to post first-quarter profit of 34 cents a share with sales of $3.63 billion, according to FactSet.",
